nl_problem:
# Task: permutations_with_duplicates
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: permuteUnique(self, arg1)

Given a collection of numbers, nums, that might contain duplicates, return all possible unique permutations in any order.

Constraints:
- 1 <= nums.length <= 8
- -10 <= nums[i] <= 10
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "permuteUnique")
  (signature ( (nums list) ) (list))
  (constraints
    (constraint "The length of nums is between 1 and 8.")
    (constraint "Each element in nums is an integer within the range -10 to 10, inclusive.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Generate all possible unique permutations from a collection of numbers that may contain duplicates. Return them in any order.")
    (rule "The output should be a list containing lists, where each inner list represents a unique permutation of the input nums.")
    (return "A list of lists representing all unique permutations of the input nums. If there are no valid permutations due to constraints, return an empty list.")
  )
)
